<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width" />
    <title>Selected Work | Chris Richel Ong</title>

    <style>
      body {
        margin: 0;
        background: #ffffff;
        color: #111111;
        font-family: system-ui, -apple-system, Segoe UI, Roboto, sans-serif;
      }

      /* KEEP HOME STYLE HEADER FEEL */
      header {
        display: flex;
        align-items: center;
        justify-content: space-between;
        padding: 24px 60px;
        border-bottom: 1px solid #e5e5e5;
      }

      nav {
        display: flex;
        gap: 28px;
        flex: 1;
        justify-content: center;
      }

      /* PAGE LAYOUT */
      main {
        max-width: 900px;
        margin: 0 auto;
        padding: 20px 24px;
      }

      h1 {
        font-size: 64px;
        line-height: 1.1;
        margin-bottom: 16px;
      }

      p.subtitle {
        font-size: 20px;
        line-height: 1.7;
        color: #444;
        max-width: 700px;
        margin-bottom: 40px;
      }

      h2 {
        font-size: 36px;
        margin-bottom: 20px;
      }

      /* 2-COLUMN CASE STUDY */
      .case {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: 200px 1fr;
        gap: 24px;
        align-items: start;
        margin-bottom: 50px;
      }

      @media (max-width: 700px) {
        .case {
          grid-template-columns: 1fr;
        }
      }

      .thumb {
  width: 100%;
  height: 260px;
  object-fit: cover;
  object-position: top;
  border-radius: 12px;
  border: 1px solid #eee;
  cursor: pointer;
  transition: transform 0.2s ease;
}

.thumb:hover {
  transform: scale(1.03);
}

      .text p {
        color: #555;
        line-height: 1.6;
        margin: 0 0 12px 0;
      }

      ul {
        margin: 10px 0 0 18px;
        color: #555;
        line-height: 1.6;
      }

      /* LIGHTBOX */
      #lightbox {
        display: none;
        position: fixed;
        inset: 0;
        background: rgba(0,0,0,0.9);
        z-index: 9999;
      }

      #lightbox img {
        max-width: 95vw;
        max-height: 85vh;
        margin: auto;
        display: block;
      }
    </style>
  </head>

  <body>

    <!-- HEADER (UNCHANGED STYLE) -->
    <header>
      <div style="font-size:20px; font-weight:600;">
        Chris Richel Ong
      </div>

      <nav>
        <a href="/" style="text-decoration:none; color:#111;">Home</a>
        <a href="/work" style="text-decoration:none; color:#16a34a; font-weight:600;">Work</a>
        <a href="/about" style="text-decoration:none; color:#111;">About</a>
      </nav>

      <a href="mailto:chrisrichelong@gmail.com"
         style="background:#16a34a;color:white;padding:14px 22px;border-radius:999px;text-decoration:none;font-weight:600;">
        Email an inquiry
      </a>
    </header>

    <main>

      <h1>Selected Work</h1>

      <p class="subtitle">
        Below are examples of improvements made to real business communication and the results that followed.
      </p>

      <!-- WEBSITE -->
      <h2>Websites</h2>

      <div class="case">

  <!-- LEFT: IMAGE WRAPPER -->
  <div style="position:relative;">

    <img class="thumb"
         src="/work/case-01-web-01.png"
         onclick="openLightbox(this.src)" 
         style="cursor:pointer;" />

    <!-- subtle label -->
    <div style="
      position:absolute;
      bottom:10px;
      left:10px;
      background:rgba(0,0,0,0.6);
      color:white;
      font-size:12px;
      padding:6px 10px;
      border-radius:999px;
      pointer-events:none;
    ">
      Click to view full page
    </div>

  </div>

  <!-- RIGHT: TEXT -->
  <div class="text">
    <p>
This project involved improving how an online product was presented so that customers could understand it faster and make decisions with more confidence.    </p>
There was a strong improvement after adding these elements:<p>
    <p><b>What was improved:</b></p>

    <ul>
      <li>Trust signals as proof that the business is legitimate (testimonials, “legit check” section, ecommerce proof)</li>
      <li>Made the offer easier to understand and added a strong guarantee</li>
      <li>Reorganized content and sections so it flows better (problem, what people wanted, examples/case study)</li>
      <li>Improved check-out experience (added payment details and sidebar trust elements)</li>
    </ul>

    <p style="margin-top:12px;">
      <b>Result:</b> The page improved from <strong>an average of 17% to above 30%</strong> after improving clarity, trust and presentation.
    </p>
  </div>

</div>

      <!-- EMAILS -->
      <h2>Emails</h2>

      <div class="case">
        <img class="thumb"
             src="/work/case-01-email-01.png"
             onclick="openLightbox(this.src)" />

        <div class="text">
          <p>
            This project focused on nurturing potential customers after they joined a Facebook group and gave their email.
            A 7-day sequence was written to nurture them and demonstrate the benefits of the product.
          </p>

          <p><b>The sequence was written using:</b></p>
          <ul>
            <li>Storytelling to explain the experience of the product</li>
            <li>Clear focus on common problems customers were facing</li>
            <li>Language customers used to described their problems</li>
          </ul>

          <p style="margin-top:12px;">
            <b>Result:</b> The email sequence achieved <strong>65.44% open rate and 11.48% click rate</strong>, showing strong engagement and interest from potential customers during the decision process.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

    </main>

    <!-- LIGHTBOX -->
    <div id="lightbox" onclick="closeLightbox()">
      <img id="lightbox-img" />
    </div>

    <script>
  function openLightbox(src) {
    console.log("opening:", src);

    const box = document.getElementById("lightbox");
    const img = document.getElementById("lightbox-img");

    if (!box || !img) {
      alert("Lightbox missing from page");
      return;
    }

    img.src = src;
    box.style.display = "flex";
    document.body.style.overflow = "hidden";
  }

  function closeLightbox() {
    const box = document.getElementById("lightbox");
    const img = document.getElementById("lightbox-img");

    box.style.display = "none";
    img.src = "";
    document.body.style.overflow = "auto";
  }

  // safety check (helps debugging)
  window.openLightbox = openLightbox;
  window.closeLightbox = closeLightbox;
</script>

    <div id="lightbox"
     onclick="closeLightbox()"
     style="
       display:none;
       position:fixed;
       inset:0;
       background:rgba(0,0,0,0.9);
       z-index:99999;
       align-items:center;
       justify-content:center;
     ">

  <img id="lightbox-img"
       style="
         max-width:95vw;
         max-height:85vh;
         object-fit:contain;
         border-radius:10px;
       " />
</div>

  </body>
</html>